defaultften appear to be based on a wholly unrealistic assessment of what changes are actually needed to implement any proposals and what management and due diligence processes are needed to ensure that any changes are correctly implemented. There is a need for c
defaultonsultation with business and professional advisers at an early stage to identify in detail what needs to be done and by whom
default so that such processes can be built in to any 
defaultcostings
default.
default&#xa0;
default41.default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn relation to the second point, w
defaulthile generally the process has improved there have been some examples where this has not been the case. 
defaultI
defaultf we take RTI again, we raised numerous concerns during the consultation process, particularly in respect of the timetable and the need to submit returns ‘on or before’ the payment date. While there have been welcome changes made as a result of the consult
defaultation process, we believe there should have been greater prior recognition of the potential problems and how they could have been addressed. 
defaultWe 
defaultalso 
defaulthave similar concerns with the rules 
defaultthat were 
defaultintroduced imposing an annual tax on enveloped dwellings
